:::

Coefficient plots from fixed effects panel models of democracy (blue) and income inequality (green). The error bars show the 95% confidence intervals. The sample includes 368 constitutions used in 165 countries with data from as early as 1920 to 2019. The models include one-year lags of the dependent variables which explain most of the variance but were omitted from the charts.
:::

